bolt URL and auth from the container instead of assuming it's localhost. While this guideline reiterates the dependency and image setup, it doesn’t restate deterministic entries. I think it might be helpful to add instructions for environment variables or system properties in the agent guidance section.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The Neo4j Java Driver's normal usage is to create a Driver for a Bolt endpoint and run Cypher against a Neo4j server; upstream tests also include Testcontainers' Neo4j module, so end-to-end driver/session/query coverage needs a live Neo4j instance rather than only the generated unit scaffold.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.testcontainers:neo4j:1.19.8\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Provides Neo4jContainer so tests can start a disposable Neo4j server for real Bolt driver/session/query coverage.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"docker_image\",\n      \"image\": \"neo4j:5.26.27-community\",\n      \"slug\": \"neo4j-5-26-community\",\n      \"reason\": \"Pinned Neo4j community server image compatible with the 5.x Java driver for live Bolt query tests.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For live-driver tests, start a Neo4jContainer with an explicit admin password and obtain the Bolt URI and credentials from the container; do not assume an external localhost:7687 server. Keep the existing in-memory Value/object-mapping tests for the reported failure path, because that specific failure may not require a server.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported failing test is in object mapping and may be fixable without Docker; live Neo4j setup is for broader meaningful driver coverage.\",\n    \"Using Testcontainers in native-image tests can add startup time and may require native metadata already present for the pinned Testcontainers version to remain compatible.\",\n    \"Neo4j Docker images are larger than typical service images and may increase CI pull time.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_050afedd7cab471c016a42931657348196b4f8f4d143667cf3\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 668, "output": 907, "cacheRead": 37888, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39463, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782747912131, "responseId": "resp_050afedd7cab471c016a4293089e408196a2fc8a43338bf30a"}, "toolResults": []}
